    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Consul at Tsingtao (
                        Hawthorne
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1405</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1405</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-06-06T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1405" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1405">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00B/6–649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hawthorne</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-06">June 6,
                            1949.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 5—11:53 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>243. President Soviet Citizens Society, accompanied by Danish Consul, Saturday
                    attempted call CC Military Headquarters apply vehicle passes, refused admission,
                    although reportedly a liaison officer to deal with such matters has been
                    appointed.</p>
                <p>Although orders to sentries still somewhat confused, now possible foreigners
                    including American staff enter, leave Consulate General and believe
                    communications can be maintained.</p>
                <p>Exchange rate announced today US $1 equals 5.50 PN;<note n="60" xml:id="d1405fn60">People’s Notes (Chinese Communist currency).</note> Yuan
                    Shihkai $1 ditto; gold bars PN 45,000 per ounce.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking 177; repeated Department 243, Shanghai 95.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hawthorne</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
